snippet: Net profit at the airline fell 8 percent for its fiscal year, pressured by Europe’s flagging economy and high unemployment.
abstract: Ryanair reports quarterly profit of 523 million euros, or $716 million, down 8 percent from 569 million euros in year-ago quarter; sales rose 3 percent to 5 billion euros.
lead_paragraph: Net profit at the airline fell 8 percent for its fiscal year, pressured by Europe’s flagging economy and high unemployment.

headline.main: Ryanair Feels the Squeeze as Rivals Lower Fares
headline.print_headline: A Year of Dropping Fares Drags Down Ryanair’s Profit
